# OpenCluely configuration
# OpenCluely answers locally via Ollama — no cloud API key required.
# Install Ollama from https://ollama.com/download; onboarding pulls the model.

# Speech Recognition
# Speech is transcribed locally by the built-in whisper.cpp engine — no cloud,
# no API key, no Python. The voice model (ggml) is downloaded by the onboarding
# wizard into a stable app-data folder. config.js supplies sensible defaults, so
# nothing below is required; uncomment to override the resident whisper-server.
# WHISPER_HOST=127.0.0.1
# WHISPER_PORT=0
# WHISPER_MODEL=small.en
# WHISPER_LANGUAGE=en
# WHISPER_THREADS=0
# WHISPER_NO_SPEECH_THRESHOLD=0.6
